<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-758] SFTP Producer - Doesn&apos;t handle folder already exists when trying to create the remote folder</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-758</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SFTP (the secure) has this bug that it doesn&apos;t check if the folder already exsits before it tries to create the remote folder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See nabble:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/SftpProducer-bug-td18640519s22882.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/SftpProducer-bug-td18640519s22882.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bela the reported want to contribute a patch later, or he will be able to test it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
